      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "I think the right approach might not be a warning. Since` -listenonion `defaults to` true`, we start `StartTorControl`\n by default. If we are still accepting incoming Tor connections, my suggestion is that we should try to make the count correct for `-netinfo`.\n\nTwo possible solutions come to mind(I have not tested any, so I don't know if they are accurate)\nOption 1 \nOverride `-listenonion` If `-bind `is specified and no `=onion` is in the bind list, automatically set` listenonion=0`:\nNo Tor hidden service created\nUser gets exactly what their` -bind` implies\n`-netinfo` gets correct count\n\nOption 2 \n Enforce `=onion `binding If -bind is specified and `listenonion=true`, and `no =onion `is in the bind list, automatically add `127.0.0.1:8334=onion:`\nTor socket created \n`inbound_onion=true` \n-netinfo Count is accurate\n\n",
